projectInfo.name: Peru Earthquake: Lagunas Buildings
projectInfo.shortDescription: Following the impact of an 8.0 magnitude earthquake in north central Peru, HOT has activated to aid response efforts. This project is to digitize buildings in the town of Lagunas, in Loreto province, Peru.
projectInfo.description:
Following the impact of an 8.0 magnitude earthquake in north central Peru, HOT has activated to aid response efforts. This project is to digitize buildings in the town of Lagunas, in Loreto province, Peru.

Please use Bing imagery to digitize buildings.
projectInfo.instructions:
*Imagery*

-Bing Imagery (the default imagery in iD editor) is the best imagery for the area.

-Please do align the imagery with existing roads or GPS traces. 

-You are free to check other imagery, it may be older, but especially if Bing Imagery has cloud coverage it might be useful to compare. 

-Mark your task only as Bad Imagery if it is either cloudy or if there is no hi-resolution imagery available. Often on slower connections it takes a moment for the imagery to start tiling in. 

-------
*Buildings*

-Most buildings are rectangular, after drawing the outline, use the 's' key in the iD web editor to "square" the corners.

-For circular buildings there is the 'o' key in the iD editor to create a circular structure.

-Please accurately outline all the buildings you can find. The outline should be for the full size of the building even if it is partly covered by trees in the imagery.

-Many buildings are very close, but do not actually touch each other, try to map them close to each other without letting them connect or share nodes with each other, roads or residential area outlines. In the iD editor, holding down the "alt" key will keep nodes of "snapping" to each other and accidentally connecting.

-The first time you map a building you will use the "Building Features" category (in the iD editor) and then at the top of the list select "Building" again, this is the most generic building tag we can use as we almost never can tell the more specific use of any building from imagery alone.

-If you have personal knowledge of a building, please add that information to the building. This can be the name or type of building (hospital, school, gas station, etc.).

-Mapping rectangular buildings:
![Animated gif of round building in iD](http://learnosm.org/images/hot-tips/rectangular_building.gif)

-Mapping circular buildings::
![Animated gif of round building in iD](https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/w/images/8/80/Round-blds-id.gif)
